Description:
Period Charm, Love the Location!
Offering a convenient lifestyle, this charming, 3 bedroom home has loads of potential together with the right location & block size.
Endearing, period flare with extra-high ceilings, block front, picture rails - here's your chance to make this gem shine!
The floorplan includes: 3 large bedrooms, separate living room, kitchen/meals. Updated bathroom & sep laundry. Side drive to garage. Fantastic backyard on good sized block of approx 460sqm.
Ideal location with bus at your door step, easy access to CityLink and tram & train just a short walk away! Approx 7.5km to the CBD & great schools nearby.
Create your dream here!

Description:
Contemporary Excellence in a Picture-Perfect Setting
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST: Closing Friday 20th Sept at 3.00pm
In a boutique complex with the open spaces of Brosnan Community Park across the road, this first-floor corner apartment delivers an exceptional low-maintenance lifestyle with its versatile design, quality inclusions and secure surrounds. Immaculate from start to finish, the home's inviting interior comprises a central hallway accessing two generous bedrooms (both with built-in robes and ceiling fans) and study, along with a superb modern ensuite, equally-stylish main bathroom and separate WC. Add to this a spacious and light-filled open living/dining area enhanced by a well-appointed kitchen with large pantry, stainless steel cooking appliances and Bosch dishwasher. Other stand-out features include a sunny north-facing balcony (from the living area) with parkland views, split-system heating and cooling, plantation shutters all-round, full-size laundry, plus secure entry foyer, undercover parking space and large storage locker. A short stroll to Merri Creek trails and parkland, childcare centre, Coburg Lake and swimming pool, it's also close to Coburg High School as well as easy access to Coburg Station, Sydney Road trams, cafes and cosmopolitan shopping precinct.

Description:
Stylish and Secluded in Coburg's Heartland
One of only three, this contemporary two-level townhouse is set to impress with its quality features, well-proportioned rooms and abundance of natural light - perfectly positioned for ultimate urban convenience offering immediate access to Coburg's key lifestyle attractions. Flawless presentation throughout, the home's inviting interior comprises two large bedrooms (both with built-in robes), stylish central bathroom with stone-top vanity and additional powder room (second WC). Add to this a spacious open-plan living/dining area accompanied by a well-appointed kitchen complete with stone benchtops, tiled splashbacks, Blanco cooking appliances and DeLonghi dishwasher. Other highlights include Daikin split-system heating and cooling, solar/gas hot water, plantation shutters, high ceilings throughout, under-stair storeroom and concealed laundry facilities. Double doors from the living area reveal a substantial north-facing courtyard with high fences for added privacy, two storage sheds and secure carport (remote-control rollerdoor to ROW). The best of Coburg at your fingertips, it's walking distance to Coburg Station, Sydney Road trams, cafes and restaurants, boutique shops and major supermarkets as well as easy access to parks and schools.

Secluded and Stylish in Coburg's Heartland
Set at the rear in a boutique block of four, this impeccable 2BR villa makes a perfect choice for professionals, investors and downsizers alike with its generous indoor/outdoor space, quality features throughout and prized location with immediate access to the best of Coburg. Spotless interior showcases a large master bedroom with WIR, second bedroom with BIRs and stylish central bathroom including separate shower and bath. Add to this a spacious front lounge leading through to the contemporary kitchen/meals area complete with tiled splashbacks, modern stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. Description:
Design Excellence with Luxury and Location
Signature style, premium inclusions and outstanding flexibility come together in this boldly-extended Victorian home delivering an aspirational family lifestyle of opulence and elegance in one of Coburg's widest streetscapes. Meticulous attention to detail, the refined interior showcases five spacious bedrooms (all with built-in robes), separate home office/sitting room, dedicated study alcove with built-in workstation and two stylish modern bathrooms. Ideal for entertaining, the home also boasts a versatile lounge and expansive open-plan living/dining area accompanied by a beautifully-appointed kitchen complete with stone benchtops, soft-close drawers, Fisher & Paykel appliances and large butler's pantry. Other luxuries include hydronic heating and split-system air conditioning, open fireplaces, high pressed-metal ceilings and solid hardwood floors, CCTV and excellent storage spaces throughout. Outside discover a north-facing backyard with bluestone-paved entertaining area, gas-heated plunge pool/spa, plus a remote-control garage (via ROW) with internal entry. Opposite the Soudan Street playground, it's also walking distance to Bell Street buses and Melville Road trams, local cafes and Coburg North Primary School, as well as easy access to Coburg Station and Sydney Road's cosmopolitan shopping precinct.

Description:
Stylish Indoor-Outdoor Living
Positioned for lifestyle enjoyment, this spacious three bedroom street frontage townhouse is a short walk to Coburg train station, Upfield Bike Path, Coburg Village, Coburg Primary and High Schools plus Sydney Road shops, cafes and trams. Executing the reverse floor plan with ease, the upstairs open plan living domain enjoys abundant light, features a fully appointed stone topped kitchen and extends to a covered terrace. Description:
Choice corner: opportunities await.
Presiding over a corner allotment of approximately 524m2, this double fronted three bedroom home and automotive garage provide tempting opportunities for investors and developers (subject to council approval). Consider transforming the Californian Bungalow style home or building stylish new residences to capitalise on the site's accessibility (subject to council approval), which is enhanced by a rear ROW. Comprising a lounge, kitchen/meals and covered outdoor area, the home has OSP at the front. Currently leased by an automotive service business at $1340 per calendar month, the garage makes this a rare offering in an increasingly sought after locale. Shore Reserve, schools, Melville Road trams and Good Times Coffee are a stroll, CityLink access a short drive and buzzing Sydney Road nearby.

Description:
SOLD - $962,500
An outstanding family opportunity in a popular setting near schools and parks, this three bedroom plus study home presents exceptional living spaces and easy outdoor entertaining. Opulent interiors feature an arched entrance hall and ornate ceilings adding an element of prestige through formal lounge and dining complete with bay windows and lavish fireplace. A brightly updated kitchen/meals featuring 900mm Smeg range oversees expansive informal living, opening to north-facing easy-care gardens offering relaxed outdoor entertaining. Excellence continues through a designer bathroom, ducted heating, refrigerated cooling, and huge double tandem garage with workshop including a remote door and internal access. All set in a community spirited locale that enjoys the convenience of Batman & Coburg Railway Stations, Coburg North Village shopping precinct, Coburg North Primary School, Sydney Road shops and cafÃ©s, Farmer's Market, Coburg Lake, and the Merri Creek bike trail.

Description:
Secluded Style with Surprising Indoor/Outdoor Space!
This distinctive townhouse, tucked away in a private Coburg cul-de-sac, presents an outstanding environment of low-maintenance style and inner-urban convenience - all just moments from Merri Creek trails and acres of parkland. Across two spacious levels, the home's light-filled interior comprises three bedrooms (extra-large master with full-width mirrored robes) and two bathrooms, expansive open-plan lounge and dining areas complemented by a central kitchen with granite benchtops and stainless steel cooking appliances. Other features include panel heating, laundry and under-stair storage space, deep garage (r/c) and additional front off-street parking, plus an undercover balcony and surprisingly large rear courtyard - fully decked, north-facing and wonderfully private. Easy access to a range of lifestyle attractions including local cafes and schools, shops and supermarkets, an endless array of restaurants as well as a choice of tramlines to university/hospital precincts and the CBD.
